A seven year-old primary pupil in a Kubwa primary school on Wednesday slumped and died on the pitch where he was playing football with his school mates. Sunday Okwuobodo, was said to have slumped after heading the ball while he was playing on the school’s football pitch during the morning break. Our reporter who visited the school on Thursday also learnt that Master Sunday was immediately rushed to the Kubwa General Hospital by some teachers where he was confirmed to have died by a medical doctor. When contacted, the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) of Kubwa, CSP Ayobami Surajudeen, confirmed the incident, adding that the family of the deceased had since been contacted while the remains was deposited at the Kubwa general hospital.